    What is the symbol for email?
    A symbol for email. Depicted as the back of an envelope imprinted with a capital letter E (for electronic) or @ (at) sign. Commonly used as an icon before an email address. The envelope is generally white with the E or @ symbols shown in blue.

    What are the email icons?
    Email icons are small graphical symbols that can be added to email messages to convey specific meanings or actions. These icons serve as visual cues, providing users with a quick and easy way to understand the purpose or urgency of an email without reading its entire content.30 Jun 2023
